observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a. OIC – Municipal Treasurer to maintain a Real Property Tax Account Register/Taxpayer’s index card as the basis for the certified list of taxpayers;
b. OIC – Municipal Treasurer to provide the Municipal Accountant with the certified list showing the name of taxpayers, and the amount due and collectible as the basis of the latter in setting-up Real Property Tax Receivables and Special Education Tax Receivables at the beginning of the year for CY 2021;
c. Municipal Accountant to draw Journal Entry Voucher to set up Real Property Tax Receivables/Special Education Tax Receivables at the beginning of the year;
d. OIC – Municipal Treasurer to come up with a certified list of taxpayers with the uncollected amount of RPT and SET Receivables from CYs 2002-2020, and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant for recording/reconciliation; and
e. Municipal Accountant to reconciled her records with the records of the OIC – Municipal Treasurer and make the necessary adjustment, if necessary.
Moving forward, instruct the OIC – Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to strictly comply with Section 20 of the MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
a. discontinue using the expense method in recording inventory;
b. device a control mechanism to ensure monitoring of issuance or consumption
of inventoriable items, including preparation of RIS;
c. recognize expense portion using SSMI; and
d. strictly comply with the instructions under Section 114 and 121 of the MNGAS.
